{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QgDKFDJt7L7sPn9TQ6S4TE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Getting Started\n2\t\n3\t> **Pre-release notice.** 0.6.0 has not yet been published to\n4\t> crates.io / PyPI / npm. This page previews the install paths\n5\t> that will be available when the GA tag fires. For current\n6\t> status see `release-notes/0.6.0.md`.\n7\t\n8\t## Planned installation (post-GA)\n9\t\n10\tWhen `v0.6.0` is published:\n11\t\n12\t### Python\n13\t\n14\t```bash\n15\tpip install fathomdb==0.6.0\n16\t```\n17\t\n18\t```python\n19\tfrom fathomdb import Engine\n20\t\n21\tengine = Engine.open(\"./my.db\")\n22\treceipt = engine.write([{\"kind\": \"doc\", \"body\": \"hello\"}])\n23\tresult = engine.search(\"hello\")\n24\tengine.close()\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\t### TypeScript / Node.js\n28\t\n29\t```bash\n30\tnpm install fathomdb@0.6.0\n31\t```\n32\t\n33\t```ts\n34\timport { Engine } from \"fathomdb\";\n35\t\n36\tconst engine = await Engine.open(\"./my.db\");\n37\tconst receipt = await engine.write([{ kind: \"doc\", body: \"hello\" }]);\n38\tconst result = await engine.search(\"hello\");\n39\tawait engine.close();\n40\t```\n41\t\n42\t> TypeScript SDK is not yet Python-parity. See\n43\t> `release-notes/0.6.0.md` § \"TypeScript SDK parity\".\n44\t\n45\t### Rust\n46\t\n47\t```toml\n48\t[dependencies]\n49\tfathomdb = \"0.6.0\"\n50\t```\n51\t\n52\tOr for the CLI:\n53\t\n54\t```bash\n55\tcargo install fathomdb-cli --version 0.6.0\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\t## What's in the box (preview)\n59\t\n60\t- Five-verb runtime SDK: `Engine.open`, `write`, `search`,\n61\t  `close`, `admin.configure`.\n62\t- Engine-attached instrumentation: `drain`, `counters`,\n63\t  `set_profiling`, `set_slow_threshold_ms`, host-logger attach.\n64\t- CLI verbs: `fathomdb doctor` (integrity checks,\n65\t  safe-export, recovery info) and `fathomdb recover`\n66\t  (accept-data-loss path). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x.\n67\t- Local-first storage on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n68\t- Two-axis versioning: workspace lockstep plus the independently\n69\t  versioned `fathomdb-embedder-api` trait crate.\n70\t\n71\t## Editable install from source (current)\n72\t\n73\tUntil 0.6.0 publishes, the only install path is from source on\n74\tthe `0.6.0-rewrite` branch:\n75\t\n76\t```bash\n77\tgit clone https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb\n78\tcd fathomdb\n79\tgit checkout 0.6.0-rewrite\n80\tpip install -e src/python/\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\tThis builds the PyO3 binding via maturin against the local Rust\n84\tworkspace.\n85\t\n86\tFor TypeScript:\n87\t\n88\t```bash\n89\tcd src/ts && npm install && npm run build\n90\t```\n91\t\n92\tFor Rust:\n93\t\n94\t```bash\n95\tcargo build --workspace\n96\t```\n97\t\n98\t## Next steps\n99\t\n100\t- `guides/` — task-based walkthroughs (post-GA).\n101\t- `concepts/` — data model + lifecycle (post-GA).\n102\t- `reference/` — public API surface (post-GA).\n103\t- `release-notes/0.6.0.md` — what's deferred + what ships.\n104\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"b0b4e4e1-4792-4aa3-bb33-5680aa252139","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:12.779Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/docs/getting-started/index.md","content":"# Getting Started\n\n> **Pre-release notice.** 0.6.0 has not yet been published to\n> crates.io / PyPI / npm. This page previews the install paths\n> that will be available when the GA tag fires. For current\n> status see `release-notes/0.6.0.md`.\n\n## Planned installation (post-GA)\n\nWhen `v0.6.0` is published:\n\n### Python\n\n```bash\npip install fathomdb==0.6.0\n```\n\n```python\nfrom fathomdb import Engine\n\nengine = Engine.open(\"./my.db\")\nreceipt = engine.write([{\"kind\": \"doc\", \"body\": \"hello\"}])\nresult = engine.search(\"hello\")\nengine.close()\n```\n\n### TypeScript / Node.js\n\n```bash\nnpm install fathomdb@0.6.0\n```\n\n```ts\nimport { Engine } from \"fathomdb\";\n\nconst engine = await Engine.open(\"./my.db\");\nconst receipt = await engine.write([{ kind: \"doc\", body: \"hello\" }]);\nconst result = await engine.search(\"hello\");\nawait engine.close();\n```\n\n> TypeScript SDK is not yet Python-parity. See\n> `release-notes/0.6.0.md` § \"TypeScript SDK parity\".\n\n### Rust\n\n```toml\n[dependencies]\nfathomdb = \"0.6.0\"\n```\n\nOr for the CLI:\n\n```bash\ncargo install fathomdb-cli --version 0.6.0\n```\n\n## What's in the box (preview)\n\n- Five-verb runtime SDK: `Engine.open`, `write`, `search`,\n  `close`, `admin.configure`.\n- Engine-attached instrumentation: `drain`, `counters`,\n  `set_profiling`, `set_slow_threshold_ms`, host-logger attach.\n- CLI verbs: `fathomdb doctor` (integrity checks,\n  safe-export, recovery info) and `fathomdb recover`\n  (accept-data-loss path). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x.\n- Local-first storage on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n- Two-axis versioning: workspace lockstep plus the independently\n  versioned `fathomdb-embedder-api` trait crate.\n\n## Editable install from source (current)\n\nUntil 0.6.0 publishes, the only install path is from source on\nthe `0.6.0-rewrite` branch:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb\ncd fathomdb\ngit checkout 0.6.0-rewrite\npip install -e src/python/\n```\n\nThis builds the PyO3 binding via maturin against the local Rust\nworkspace.\n\nFor TypeScript:\n\n```bash\ncd src/ts && npm install && npm run build\n```\n\nFor Rust:\n\n```bash\ncargo build --workspace\n```\n\n## Next steps\n\n- `guides/` — task-based walkthroughs (post-GA).\n- `concepts/` — data model + lifecycle (post-GA).\n- `reference/` — public API surface (post-GA).\n- `release-notes/0.6.0.md` — what's deferred + what ships.\n","numLines":104,"startLine":1,"totalLines":104}}}
