{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JHYmHV5TftB74GaVAAJgGk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 0.6.0 Release Notes (Preview)\n2\t\n3\t**Status: pre-release.** `0.6.0` is on the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch\n4\tand has not yet been published to crates.io / PyPI / npm. This\n5\tpage previews what 0.6.0 will deliver when the GA tag fires.\n6\t\n7\t## What 0.6.0 delivers\n8\t\n9\t### Engine + storage substrate\n10\t\n11\t- Local-first retrieval engine on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n12\t- Canonical writes, vector projections, scheduler, op-store,\n13\t  reader pool with thread-affine workers.\n14\t- Typed error hierarchy: `EngineError` plus structured leaves\n15\t  (`StorageError`, `ProjectionError`, `VectorError`,\n16\t  `EmbedderError`, `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`,\n17\t  `KindNotVectorIndexedError`, `SchedulerError`, `OpStoreError`,\n18\t  `WriteValidationError`, `SchemaValidationError`,\n19\t  `OverloadedError`, `ClosingError`, `DatabaseLockedError`,\n20\t  `CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`).\n21\t- Five-verb runtime SDK surface: `Engine.open`, `engine.write`,\n22\t  `engine.search`, `engine.close`, `admin.configure`.\n23\t- Engine-attached instrumentation: `engine.drain`,\n24\t  `engine.counters`, `engine.set_profiling`,\n25\t  `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms`, host logging subscriber attach.\n26\t\n27\t### Bindings\n28\t\n29\t- **Python SDK** (`fathomdb`) — PyO3 binding. Type stubs at\n30\t  `fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. Public surface locked at\n31\t  `dev/interfaces/python.md` (internal spec).\n32\t- **TypeScript SDK** (`fathomdb`) — napi-rs binding. Promise API,\n33\t  handoff pool, typed exception envelope.\n34\t- **Rust facade crate** (`fathomdb`) — re-exports the runtime\n35\t  verbs from `fathomdb-engine` for downstream Rust consumers.\n36\t- **CLI** (`fathomdb-cli`) — `doctor` and `recover` verbs\n37\t  (Phase 10a). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x — see below.\n38\t\n39\t### Release engineering\n40\t\n41\t- Two-axis versioning: Axis W (workspace lockstep across the\n42\t  six runtime/binding/CLI crates + Python + TS packages); Axis E\n43\t  (`fathomdb-embedder-api` independent — trait surface stability\n44\t  per ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol).\n45\t- 8-tier topological publish order via `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n46\t  with crates.io index-propagation sleeps between tiers and\n47\t  post-publish smoke against fresh installs from each registry.\n48\t- Single brand: `fathomdb` on crates.io / PyPI / npm.\n49\t- `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces axis lockstep\n50\t  pre-publish; pre-push hook runs the check before agent-verify.\n51\t- actionlint v1.7.7 wired as canonical workflow validator.\n52\t\n53\t## What is deferred (will not ship in 0.6.0 GA)\n54\t\n55\tThese are documented and will appear in the final GA release\n56\tnotes verbatim.\n57\t\n58\t### Performance gates (4 ACs)\n59\t\n60\tPerformance acceptance criteria **AC-012**, **AC-013**, **AC-019**,\n61\t**AC-020** are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17\n62\tper Phase 12-P decision). Engine surfaces them as documented gates,\n63\tnot weakened ones. See `dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution\n64\tfor the canonical rationale and Pack 7 remediation track.\n65\t\n66\t- **AC-012** text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms):\n67\t  closes in **0.6.1** via canonical-runner re-measurement (dev\n68\t  runner is aarch64 Tegra ~3× slower than canonical x86_64). No\n69\t  engine code change expected.\n70\t- **AC-013** vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms):\n71\t  closes via **Pack 7** batched-insert vec0 API (current bulk-seed\n72\t  is engine-surface gap, not retrieval-path issue).\n73\t- **AC-019** mixed-retrieval stress tail: closes via Pack 7\n74\t  (inherits AC-013 substrate).\n75\t- **AC-020** N=8 concurrent reader scaling: **architectural gap**.\n76\t  Best speedup on dev runner 3.53× vs required ≥ 5.33×; residual\n77\t  is `pcache1` mutex acquires on every page-fetch (hit-path).\n78\t  Closure requires Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work\n79\t  (`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` custom allocator OR WAL2 OR\n80\t  reader/writer physical separation OR vendor-SQLite swap). Pack\n81\t  5 + Pack 6 + Pack 6.G falsified every canonical-SQLite lever\n82\t  measurable on the AC-020 fixture.\n83\t\n84\t### `Engine.open` structured open report\n85\t\n86\tBoth Python and TypeScript SDKs currently return only the engine handle\n87\tfrom `Engine.open`. The structured open report (migration-version-\n88\treached, embedder-identity-confirmed, open-stage data) defined in\n89\t`design/engine.md` and called for by `interfaces/{python,typescript}.md`\n90\tis populated on the native Rust side (`OpenedEngine.report`) but\n91\t**dropped by both bindings in 0.6.0**.\n92\t\n93\tSurfacing the open report defers to **0.6.1** (slice\n94\t`12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Symmetric across both bindings, so not a\n95\tTS-vs-Python parity gap. Clients depending on open-report data\n96\tshould pin to 0.6.1 when it ships.\n97\t\n98\t### Logical-id verbs\n99\t\n100\t`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` deferred to **0.7.x**\n101\t(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17 per Phase 12-V-VERBS decision). The\n102\tcanonical-identity substrate (`row_id` / `logical_id` /\n103\t`superseded_at` / `restore_provenance` columns, partial unique\n104\tindex on `(logical_id, kind)`, writer supersession step) is\n105\tdesign-only in 0.6.0 — verbs cannot be built without the substrate.\n106\t\n107\t**Client workaround for 0.6.0**: bulk-delete by source uses\n108\t`fathomdb recover --excise-source <id>` (landed in Phase 10a).\n109\tRestore-from-log workflows wait for 0.7.x.\n110\t\n111\tSee `dev/design/recovery.md` § Logical-id purge and restore for\n112\tthe design + substrate spec.\n113\t\n114\t### TypeScript SDK parity\n115\t\n116\t- TS milestone 1 shipped 2026-04-07; not yet feature-equal with\n117\t  Python. TS Python-parity is a Phase 12 deliverable (will close\n118\t  before GA tag) but lands after performance + security + verb\n119\t  decisions. Until then, prefer the Python SDK for production\n120\t  pilots.\n121\t\n122\t### Compatibility\n123\t\n124\t- **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a\n125\t  rewrite; clients on 0.5.x must follow a separate migration\n126\t  guide (not provided in 0.6.0).\n127\t\n128\t## How to follow along\n129\t\n130\t- Plan + status: `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` § Path to\n131\t  Client-Ready (0.6.0 GA).\n132\t- Public interface specs (internal-facing):\n133\t  `dev/interfaces/{rust,python,typescript,cli,wire}.md`.\n134\t- Acceptance scoreboard: `dev/acceptance.md`.\n135\t\n136\tWhen 0.6.0 GA tags, this page will be replaced with the final\n137\trelease notes including install commands for all three registries.\n138\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"f57c934a-054f-4572-a5c7-63ed1a765f0f","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:13.252Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/docs/release-notes/0.6.0.md","content":"# 0.6.0 Release Notes (Preview)\n\n**Status: pre-release.** `0.6.0` is on the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch\nand has not yet been published to crates.io / PyPI / npm. This\npage previews what 0.6.0 will deliver when the GA tag fires.\n\n## What 0.6.0 delivers\n\n### Engine + storage substrate\n\n- Local-first retrieval engine on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).\n- Canonical writes, vector projections, scheduler, op-store,\n  reader pool with thread-affine workers.\n- Typed error hierarchy: `EngineError` plus structured leaves\n  (`StorageError`, `ProjectionError`, `VectorError`,\n  `EmbedderError`, `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`,\n  `KindNotVectorIndexedError`, `SchedulerError`, `OpStoreError`,\n  `WriteValidationError`, `SchemaValidationError`,\n  `OverloadedError`, `ClosingError`, `DatabaseLockedError`,\n  `CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`).\n- Five-verb runtime SDK surface: `Engine.open`, `engine.write`,\n  `engine.search`, `engine.close`, `admin.configure`.\n- Engine-attached instrumentation: `engine.drain`,\n  `engine.counters`, `engine.set_profiling`,\n  `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms`, host logging subscriber attach.\n\n### Bindings\n\n- **Python SDK** (`fathomdb`) — PyO3 binding. Type stubs at\n  `fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. Public surface locked at\n  `dev/interfaces/python.md` (internal spec).\n- **TypeScript SDK** (`fathomdb`) — napi-rs binding. Promise API,\n  handoff pool, typed exception envelope.\n- **Rust facade crate** (`fathomdb`) — re-exports the runtime\n  verbs from `fathomdb-engine` for downstream Rust consumers.\n- **CLI** (`fathomdb-cli`) — `doctor` and `recover` verbs\n  (Phase 10a). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x — see below.\n\n### Release engineering\n\n- Two-axis versioning: Axis W (workspace lockstep across the\n  six runtime/binding/CLI crates + Python + TS packages); Axis E\n  (`fathomdb-embedder-api` independent — trait surface stability\n  per ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol).\n- 8-tier topological publish order via `.github/workflows/release.yml`\n  with crates.io index-propagation sleeps between tiers and\n  post-publish smoke against fresh installs from each registry.\n- Single brand: `fathomdb` on crates.io / PyPI / npm.\n- `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces axis lockstep\n  pre-publish; pre-push hook runs the check before agent-verify.\n- actionlint v1.7.7 wired as canonical workflow validator.\n\n## What is deferred (will not ship in 0.6.0 GA)\n\nThese are documented and will appear in the final GA release\nnotes verbatim.\n\n### Performance gates (4 ACs)\n\nPerformance acceptance criteria **AC-012**, **AC-013**, **AC-019**,\n**AC-020** are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17\nper Phase 12-P decision). Engine surfaces them as documented gates,\nnot weakened ones. See `dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution\nfor the canonical rationale and Pack 7 remediation track.\n\n- **AC-012** text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms):\n  closes in **0.6.1** via canonical-runner re-measurement (dev\n  runner is aarch64 Tegra ~3× slower than canonical x86_64). No\n  engine code change expected.\n- **AC-013** vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms):\n  closes via **Pack 7** batched-insert vec0 API (current bulk-seed\n  is engine-surface gap, not retrieval-path issue).\n- **AC-019** mixed-retrieval stress tail: closes via Pack 7\n  (inherits AC-013 substrate).\n- **AC-020** N=8 concurrent reader scaling: **architectural gap**.\n  Best speedup on dev runner 3.53× vs required ≥ 5.33×; residual\n  is `pcache1` mutex acquires on every page-fetch (hit-path).\n  Closure requires Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work\n  (`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` custom allocator OR WAL2 OR\n  reader/writer physical separation OR vendor-SQLite swap). Pack\n  5 + Pack 6 + Pack 6.G falsified every canonical-SQLite lever\n  measurable on the AC-020 fixture.\n\n### `Engine.open` structured open report\n\nBoth Python and TypeScript SDKs currently return only the engine handle\nfrom `Engine.open`. The structured open report (migration-version-\nreached, embedder-identity-confirmed, open-stage data) defined in\n`design/engine.md` and called for by `interfaces/{python,typescript}.md`\nis populated on the native Rust side (`OpenedEngine.report`) but\n**dropped by both bindings in 0.6.0**.\n\nSurfacing the open report defers to **0.6.1** (slice\n`12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Symmetric across both bindings, so not a\nTS-vs-Python parity gap. Clients depending on open-report data\nshould pin to 0.6.1 when it ships.\n\n### Logical-id verbs\n\n`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` deferred to **0.7.x**\n(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17 per Phase 12-V-VERBS decision). The\ncanonical-identity substrate (`row_id` / `logical_id` /\n`superseded_at` / `restore_provenance` columns, partial unique\nindex on `(logical_id, kind)`, writer supersession step) is\ndesign-only in 0.6.0 — verbs cannot be built without the substrate.\n\n**Client workaround for 0.6.0**: bulk-delete by source uses\n`fathomdb recover --excise-source <id>` (landed in Phase 10a).\nRestore-from-log workflows wait for 0.7.x.\n\nSee `dev/design/recovery.md` § Logical-id purge and restore for\nthe design + substrate spec.\n\n### TypeScript SDK parity\n\n- TS milestone 1 shipped 2026-04-07; not yet feature-equal with\n  Python. TS Python-parity is a Phase 12 deliverable (will close\n  before GA tag) but lands after performance + security + verb\n  decisions. Until then, prefer the Python SDK for production\n  pilots.\n\n### Compatibility\n\n- **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a\n  rewrite; clients on 0.5.x must follow a separate migration\n  guide (not provided in 0.6.0).\n\n## How to follow along\n\n- Plan + status: `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` § Path to\n  Client-Ready (0.6.0 GA).\n- Public interface specs (internal-facing):\n  `dev/interfaces/{rust,python,typescript,cli,wire}.md`.\n- Acceptance scoreboard: `dev/acceptance.md`.\n\nWhen 0.6.0 GA tags, this page will be replaced with the final\nrelease notes including install commands for all three registries.\n","numLines":138,"startLine":1,"totalLines":138}}}
