{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RbNLhQavEwsoNZ1jdHAkHP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# FathomDB Public Docs\n2\t\n3\tFathomDB is a local-first retrieval and graph-oriented data system designed for\n4\tapplication and agent workloads. This site is the public documentation source\n5\tfor users, operators, and SDK consumers.\n6\t\n7\t> **Status: 0.6.0 pre-release.** Engine + bindings + release-engineering\n8\t> substrate complete (Phase 11 closed 2026-05-17). Durability harnesses,\n9\t> security fixtures, post-publish smoke, and external-user docs land in\n10\t> Phase 12 before the `v0.6.0` GA tag. See `release-notes/0.6.0.md` for a\n11\t> preview and the deferred-items list.\n12\t\n13\tUse these sections:\n14\t\n15\t- `getting-started/` for initial setup and orientation (preview install paths)\n16\t- `guides/` for task-based workflows (post-GA)\n17\t- `concepts/` for durable public model explanations (post-GA)\n18\t- `reference/` for surface-level API and packaging notes (post-GA)\n19\t- `operations/` for runtime and maintenance guidance (post-GA)\n20\t- `positions/` for consumer-relevant technical positions\n21\t- `release-notes/0.6.0.md` for the 0.6.0 preview + deferral disclosures\n22\t- `compatibility/` for cross-version compatibility notes\n23\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"af94f9f7-892a-426f-a508-8b61dd787cf4","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:13.277Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/docs/index.md","content":"# FathomDB Public Docs\n\nFathomDB is a local-first retrieval and graph-oriented data system designed for\napplication and agent workloads. This site is the public documentation source\nfor users, operators, and SDK consumers.\n\n> **Status: 0.6.0 pre-release.** Engine + bindings + release-engineering\n> substrate complete (Phase 11 closed 2026-05-17). Durability harnesses,\n> security fixtures, post-publish smoke, and external-user docs land in\n> Phase 12 before the `v0.6.0` GA tag. See `release-notes/0.6.0.md` for a\n> preview and the deferred-items list.\n\nUse these sections:\n\n- `getting-started/` for initial setup and orientation (preview install paths)\n- `guides/` for task-based workflows (post-GA)\n- `concepts/` for durable public model explanations (post-GA)\n- `reference/` for surface-level API and packaging notes (post-GA)\n- `operations/` for runtime and maintenance guidance (post-GA)\n- `positions/` for consumer-relevant technical positions\n- `release-notes/0.6.0.md` for the 0.6.0 preview + deferral disclosures\n- `compatibility/` for cross-version compatibility notes\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
