{"type":"stream_event","event":{"type":"message_delta","delta":{"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null},"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31657,"cache_read_input_tokens":15733,"output_tokens":694,"iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":694,"cache_read_input_tokens":15733,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31657},"type":"message"}]},"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ec6e9cac-3045-4996-9a98-eb0bab7471fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016m38pfz5gBMyzKe34HSPBE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: CLI Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-05-12\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public CLI surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/lib.rs; design/recovery.md; design/errors.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# CLI Interface\n11\t\n12\tPublic CLI surface for the 0.6.0 operator binary. The canonical verb table and\n13\trecovery semantics are owned by `design/recovery.md`; this file owns concrete\n14\tflag spelling, root command paths, and exit-code classes.\n15\t\n16\t## Roots\n17\t\n18\t- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>...`\n19\t- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...`\n20\t\n21\tThe CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0. It does not mirror the SDK five-verb\n22\tapplication surface and does not ship `search` / `get` / `list` query verbs.\n23\t\n24\t## Output posture\n25\t\n26\t- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.\n27\t- `doctor check-integrity` emits a single JSON object.\n28\t- `doctor check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as\n29\t  `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.\n30\t- `recover` JSON output is a progress stream plus summary, owned by\n31\t  `design/recovery.md`.\n32\t- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly document it;\n33\t  it is not a separate machine schema.\n34\t\n35\t## Exit-code classes\n36\t\n37\t| Code | Stable meaning                                                       | Primary owner                    |\n38\t| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |\n39\t| `0`  | successful completion with no findings that require a non-zero exit  | this file                        |\n40\t| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n41\t| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n42\t| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n43\t| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n44\t| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n45\t\n46\t## Doctor verbs\n47\t\n48\t| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n49\t| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n50\t| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n51\t| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n52\t| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n53\t| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n54\t| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n55\t| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n56\t| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n57\t\n58\t`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n59\t71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n60\t\n61\t## Recover root\n62\t\n63\t`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n64\t\n65\t```text\n66\tfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n67\t  [--truncate-wal]\n68\t  [--rebuild-vec0]\n69\t  [--rebuild-projections]\n70\t  [--excise-source <id>]\n71\t```\n72\t\n73\tExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n74\t\n75\t`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\n76\treject it as unknown.\n77\t\n78\t`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\n79\tor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\n80\tbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n81\t\n82\t## Error to exit-code mapping\n83\t\n84\tThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\n85\tpreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\n86\tto its class.\n87\t\n88\t| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n89\t| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n90\t| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n91\t| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n92\t| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n93\t| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n94\t| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n95\t| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n96\t| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n97\t| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n98\t| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n99\t| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n100\t| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n101\t| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n102\t| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n103\t| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n104\t| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n105\t| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n106\t| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n107\t| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n108\t| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n109\t| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n110\t| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n111\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n112\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n113\t| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n114\t\n115\t## JSON output wrapping\n116\t\n117\t`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns\n118\ttyped report structs; the CLI serializes them under a `verb` discriminator.\n119\t\n120\t- All `--json` output is one JSON object (or an NDJSON stream for `recover`).\n121\t- Doctor verb wrapping pattern: `{ \"verb\": \"<verb-name>\", ...flattened_engine_report_fields... }`.\n122\t- Non-flat reports nest naturally. For example, `IntegrityReport` serializes\n123\t  as `{ \"verb\": \"check-integrity\", \"physical\": {...}, \"logical\": {...}, \"semantic\": {...} }`.\n124\t- Field name policy: serde default `snake_case`. Any divergence from engine\n125\t  field spellings lives in the CLI serialization layer; the engine report\n126\t  structs are not renamed to satisfy CLI spelling requirements.\n127\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"c6c589a6-9dfd-4784-b34b-2b2d95eea8fd","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:29.551Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/dev/interfaces/cli.md","content":"---\ntitle: CLI Public Interface\ndate: 2026-05-12\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public CLI surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/lib.rs; design/recovery.md; design/errors.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# CLI Interface\n\nPublic CLI surface for the 0.6.0 operator binary. The canonical verb table and\nrecovery semantics are owned by `design/recovery.md`; this file owns concrete\nflag spelling, root command paths, and exit-code classes.\n\n## Roots\n\n- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>...`\n- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...`\n\nThe CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0. It does not mirror the SDK five-verb\napplication surface and does not ship `search` / `get` / `list` query verbs.\n\n## Output posture\n\n- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.\n- `doctor check-integrity` emits a single JSON object.\n- `doctor check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as\n  `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.\n- `recover` JSON output is a progress stream plus summary, owned by\n  `design/recovery.md`.\n- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly document it;\n  it is not a separate machine schema.\n\n## Exit-code classes\n\n| Code | Stable meaning                                                       | Primary owner                    |\n| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |\n| `0`  | successful completion with no findings that require a non-zero exit  | this file                        |\n| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n\n## Doctor verbs\n\n| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n\n`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n\n## Recover root\n\n`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n\n```text\nfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n  [--truncate-wal]\n  [--rebuild-vec0]\n  [--rebuild-projections]\n  [--excise-source <id>]\n```\n\nExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n\n`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\nreject it as unknown.\n\n`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\nor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\nbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n\n## Error to exit-code mapping\n\nThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\npreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\nto its class.\n\n| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n\n## JSON output wrapping\n\n`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns\ntyped report structs; the CLI serializes them under a `verb` discriminator.\n\n- All `--json` output is one JSON object (or an NDJSON stream for `recover`).\n- Doctor verb wrapping pattern: `{ \"verb\": \"<verb-name>\", ...flattened_engine_report_fields... }`.\n- Non-flat reports nest naturally. For example, `IntegrityReport` serializes\n  as `{ \"verb\": \"check-integrity\", \"physical\": {...}, \"logical\": {...}, \"semantic\": {...} }`.\n- Field name policy: serde default `snake_case`. Any divergence from engine\n  field spellings lives in the CLI serialization layer; the engine report\n  structs are not renamed to satisfy CLI spelling requirements.\n","numLines":127,"startLine":1,"totalLines":127}}}
